TITLE: He's Got The Latest Shit T-shirt
INFO:
Roland Browning made his Grange Hill debut in 1982: coincidentally the only year that the Roland corporation was manufacturing all three of the magical machines in this picture at the same time. One year later came Roland Rat. Why this era was so rich with iconic Rolands is anyone's guess but it's something I felt worth acknowledging in Paint form.

From the Yamaha PSS-380 I first played with as a toddler trying to emulate my Dad's Jean Michel Jarre records to the Korg X3 I had as a teenager and all the classic Roland sounds I spent my 20s raving to, synths have always been my first love - before Paint, even. Like Roland Browning I was bullied at school but I always had electronic music as an escape. For that reason this piece is very special to me.

Big love and thanks to Henry Shitmat for the tagline - this is taken from his 2004 track "UK Swampcore Sucks in Comparison to Techstep New Wave Psy-Jungle" - if you know the track you'll know why I picked these words.
